s. But which one is the best? There are different answers to this question. However, if you want to be a digital influencer in 2022, I will show you why Instagram is the best.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:more -->\n<!--more-->\n<!-- /wp:more -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instagram has a high number of monthly active users, which means it is one of the most popular social media platforms. It is estimated that Instagram has more than 1.28 billion active users, which makes it the fourth most used social media platform losing only to Facebook, Youtube and Whatsapp (Dixon). However, the average engagement rate in an Instagram post is higher than any other social media platform. For example, a single Instagram post is ten times more likely to be liked, commented or shared (Feehan).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also, Instagram has the best-looking and most user-friendly interface of all social media platforms. To begin with, upper and lower level navigation bars are self-explanatory with straightforward icons that clearly translate the platform\'s features. Setting up your profile is super easy, and you still get to choose which account suits you best from being in a private, business or creator profile. Right after that, you receive a lot of relevant suggestions from people to follow. Although this should be the standard for all social media platforms, the sad reality is that most of them take more time to get used to than Instagram. Take, for example, Facebook and its massive menu of not always clear features, Snapchat and its message that automatically erase themselves, Discord and its hard-to-setup channels, TikTok and its home page default to For You instead of Following, and Clubhouse Does anyone even remember it?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Additionally, Instagram has all the features you need to be a successful digital influencer. Not more than you need, not less than you need. You can post photos and videos in multiple formats on your feed and your profile stories. Nowadays, you can post photos, boomerangs, and reels (in 15, 30, 60 and 90 seconds!), pin your favourite posts and comments, post your live day on stories, and you can select your favourites to be highlighted on your profile. You can even do a live event for thousands of people, such as a concert, a conference, a fashion show, or even a gaming session. Instagram is constantly updating and implementing new features to best suit its users to create a more engaging and fun platform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Besides, Instagrams recommendation algorithm is very effective. It relies on most of the proprietary technology from the Meta company (the same owner of Facebook), and it is crazily well trained to give users the best recommendations. It works really well for creating connections between users who share a sense of community, which can be a powerful tool for a digital influencer. It also works really well with advertisements, which can make the promotion of products, services, partnerships, and any other kind of content seem effortless.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Talking about products and services, Instagram also works really well as an e-commerce platform. It means that you dont even need to hire an expensive social media consulting firm or a big marketing agency to create a complex website and deal with all the pain and frustration of the problems that come with hosting your own e-commerce platform. You can take a picture of a product with your smartphone or create a description of a service in your notepad and use your own Instagram profile to set up a marketplace. A lot of influencers offer their own branded products on Instagram, and it is absolutely a hit!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Needless to say, most of the top influencers, companies, Hollywood celebrities, sports MVPs, rockstars, gamers, DJs, rappers, Formula One pilots, CEOs, Presidents, Prime Ministers, and all other popular media icons are very active on Instagram. Barack Obama is active on Instagram. The Kardashians are active on Instagram. Cristiano Ronaldo is active on Instagram. NASA is active on Instagram. Nike is active on Instagram. Everybody who is anybody is active on Instagram. Instagram is an awesome social media platform, and if you are a social media influencer, you should be there too!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Works Cited</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dixon, S. Instagram users worldwide 2025. Statista, 23 May 2022, <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/183585/instagram-number-of-global-users/\">https://www.statista.com/statistics/183585/instagram-number-of-global-users/</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Feehan, Blair. 2019 Social Media Industry Benchmark Report. Rival IQ, 15 February 2019, <a href=\"https://www.rivaliq.com/blog/2019-social-media-benchmark-report/\">https://www.rivaliq.com/blog/2019-social-media-benchmark-report/</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Image retrieved from: https://pixabay.com/vectors/icon-set-social-media-contact-web-1142000/</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Article: Why is Instagram the best social media for digital influencers?','Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, Snapchat, Twitter, Pinterest, Whatsapp, Youtube, WeChat, QQ, Reddit, Discord, Clubhouse, LinkedIn, Telegram and the list goes on. If you want to be a digital influencer, you have plenty of options. But which one is the best?','inherit','closed','closed','','118-autosave-v1','','','2022-08-13 03:13:03','2022-08-13 03:13:03','',118,'https://ysousa-monteiro.dragonteach.com/?p=227',0,'revision','',0),(228,1,'2022-08-13 03:13:26','2022-08-13 03:13:26','','icon-set-1142000_1280-1','','inherit','open','closed','','icon-set-1142000_1280-1','','','2022-08-13 03:13:26','2022-08-13 03:13:26','',118